Kaveel Singh, News24iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; Cape Town Law Enforcement officers have apprehended an alleged thief who broke into a car and stole &ldquo;R100 worth of Kentucky Fried Chicken [KFC]&rdquo;, an official said. Spokesperson Wayne Minaar said two officers in the Law Enforcement Transport Enforcement Unit in Mitchell&rsquo;s Plain noticed a man running after another man on Sunday.&ldquo;The man giving chase was the owner of a vehicle that was broken in to." He flagged down the officers told them what had just happened. &ldquo;The officers gave chase and apprehended the thief who had stolen R100 worth of KFC and a radio/cd player from the car." The 38-year-old suspect, who is from Eastridge in Mitchell&rsquo;s Plain, has been charged for theft out of motor vehicle. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.